f-element.title:
The TSF shall support the following for the Password Authentication Factor:
Passwords shall be able to be composed of any combination of upper and lower case letters a character set of at least 52 characters , numbers, and special characters: "!" "@" "#" "$" "%" "^" "&" "*" "(" ")" other characters ;
Password length up to an integer greater than or equal to 14 characters shall be supported.

The TSF shall, upon transitioning to the locked state, perform the following operations:
clearing or overwriting display devices, obscuring the previous contents;
other actions performed upon transitioning to the locked state.
